Lab 16: Linux Forensics Automation
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Extract and analyze system logs, processes, and network information from Linux systems
Create automated Bash and Python scripts for forensic data collection
Identify unauthorized activities using collected forensic data
Implement automated forensic workflows for incident response
Generate comprehensive forensic reports
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of file system navigation and text editors
Familiarity with system logs and processes
Basic scripting knowledge (Bash and Python)
