Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Permission denied when accessing log files

Solution: Use sudo for commands requiring root access, or run scripts as root
Issue: Commands not found (netstat, ifconfig)

Solution: Install net-tools package: sudo apt-get install net-tools
Alternative: Use modern replacements (ss, ip) which are pre-installed
Issue: Python script fails to find collection directory

Solution: Ensure forensic_collector.sh ran successfully first
Verify: Check /home/forensics/ for automated_collection_* directories
Issue: Empty or missing log files

Solution: Log locations vary by distribution; check /var/log/ contents
Alternative: Use journalctl for systemd-based logging
Conclusion
This lab introduced Linux forensics automation through hands-on data collection and analysis. Students learned to extract system logs, processes, and network information, then automate these tasks using Bash and Python scripts. The ability to detect unauthorized activities and generate forensic reports is essential for incident response and security operations.

Key takeaways:

Systematic forensic data collection preserves evidence integrity
Automation ensures consistent and repeatable forensic processes
